Definition.WordDefinition:
Outgrow \Out*grow"\, v. t. [imp. {Outgrew}; p. p. {Outgrown}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Outgrowing}.] [1913 Webster] 1. To surpass in growing; to grow more than. --Shak. [1913 Webster]
2. To grow out of or away from; to grow too large, or too aged, for; as, to outgrow clothing; to outgrow usefulness; to outgrow an infirmity. [1913 Webster]
outgrow v 1: grow too large or too mature for; "I have outgrown these clothes" 2: grow too large for [syn: {overgrow}] 3: grow faster than [also: {outgrown}, {outgrew}]
